We use a 2D array (dp) to store the result of applying the operations on the characters at the corresponding positions in the input strings. We iterate through the strings from the last character to the first character (i.e., from right to left) and from top to bottom (i.e., from left to right). We check if the characters at the current position are the same and update the corresponding cell in the dp array accordingly. The final value in the dp array indicates if a string can be converted into the other using the given operations.

